					<description><![CDATA[For this class, I was assigned to make a new feature for the game, and create a level around that feature. I had a somewhat difficult time deciding on what&#8230;]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>For this class, I was assigned to make a new feature for the game, and create a level around that feature. I had a somewhat difficult time deciding on what feature to implement and how I should design my level. Originally, I was going to create an abandoned medieval town that the player explored and solved the mystery behind it. I then realized that this would take too much time and instead opted to do a &#8220;simple&#8221; puzzle map, where the player attempts to escape from a dungeon. <em>*1</em> </p>



<p>If you want to see how I designed some of the levels, and coded one of the features, I did a few livestreams on it, so feel free to watch it if you want. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Unreal Engine Streams" width="1100" height="619" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?list=PL20GnSQO83BLFwal3new_ajmzwx3mBd9O" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<p>This is the video of my level for when I finished my Blockmesh.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Level Design 2 BlockMesh Level" width="1100" height="619" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2l2DZEo3JK0?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<p>*1: My original sentence was &#8220;I then realized that that seemed like it would take to much time and opted to do a &#8220;simple&#8221; puzzle map, where you attempt to escape from a dungeon.&#8221;  But my translator did not like my use of the double that.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
